{
  "texts": [
    "Following that, our meta-design approach used open-ended tasks and scaffolding to engage students in collaboratively exploring key classifier concepts through their own interests and app ideas.",
    "Using our own AI app development studio that does not require programming, children followed the basic epistemic functions related to ML workflows and connect their design ideas and evolving understanding to real-world contexts (Pope et al., 2024).",
    "Fig. 1 presents classroom photos from different stages of the co-design process.",
    "At the end of the project, children reflected on the potential risks and harms of AI through their own app-design process and explored algorithmic bias using generative AI (Vartiainen et al., 2024).",
    "Qualitative content analysis of pre-and post tests, children's design ideas, and reflections of the app design process revealed that co-design provided promising entry points for children to develop conceptual understanding of AI principles, workflows, and its role in everyday life."
  ]
}